<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,989,1538]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1138,1164]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is morphologically highly variable, which has led to an ongoing debate on whether this is a single species or several. Currently, in the Mediterranean a second species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Delle Chiaje, 1828" authorityName="Delle Chiaje" authorityYear="1828" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Ophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="quinquemaculata">
<collectingCountry box="[1406,1427,1176,1201]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[1406,1427,1176,1201]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">O</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,359,1213,1238]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">quinquemaculata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Delle" box="[375,607,1213,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="55" refString="Delle Chiaje, S. (1828) Memorie sulla storia e anotomia degli animali senza vertebre del Regno di Napoli, vol. 3, Stamperia della societa tipografica, Napoli [Naples], 232 p." type="book" year="1828">
Delle Chiaje, 
<number box="[544,607,1213,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1828.0">1828</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, is supposed to exist. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Baric" box="[1005,1337,1213,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="55" refString="Baric, S. &amp; Sturmbauer, C. (1999) Ecological parallelism and cryptic species in the genus Ophiothrix derived from mitochondrial DNA sequences. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 11, 157 - 162." type="journal article" year="1999">
Baric &amp; Sturmbauer (
<number box="[1266,1328,1213,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
showed that there are two distinct mt-DNA lineages that each contains individuals from both morphological species. They suggested that 
<taxonomicName box="[399,522,1288,1314]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Ophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<collectingCountry box="[399,420,1288,1313]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[399,420,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">O</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis box="[436,522,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[582,827,1288,1314]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Ophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="quinquemaculata">
<collectingCountry box="[582,603,1288,1313]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[582,603,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">O</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis box="[620,827,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">quinquemaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not different species, but ecotypes of the same species. Instead there may be a Mediterranean and a North Atlantic lineage, which may turn out to be distinct species (
<bibRefCitation author="Baric" box="[251,560,1362,1388]" pageId="9" pageNumber="55" refString="Baric, S. &amp; Sturmbauer, C. (1999) Ecological parallelism and cryptic species in the genus Ophiothrix derived from mitochondrial DNA sequences. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 11, 157 - 162." type="journal article" year="1999">
Baric &amp; Sturmbauer 
<number box="[497,560,1362,1388]" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Both nominal species have never been formally synonymised, pending a much needed revision of the whole genus. Our specimens fall within the morphological and ecological range of 
<taxonomicName box="[182,303,1437,1463]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Ophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="9" pageNumber="54" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<collectingCountry box="[182,203,1437,1462]" name="Iceland" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis box="[182,203,1437,1462]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">O</emphasis>
</collectingCountry>
. 
<emphasis box="[218,303,1437,1462]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="54">fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
